The paper deals with the analysis of spectral efficiency and signal-to-interference and noise ratios (SINRs) for asynchronous code division multiple access (CDMA) systems with random spreading. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of linear minimum mean square error (MMSE) detectors, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper provides guidelines for the design of low complexity multistage detectors, which falls under the category of computer communications (cs.COM).
